719756f-a.title: Manhattan: Forsyth Street - Division Street
719756f-a.text:
Porayth Street, at the N.E. corner of Division Street. Shown aoross the
demolition, are the rears of buildings which front on the west side of Eldridge
Street.
July 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPPODUCTIONS.

719753f-a.title: Manhattan: Forsyth Street - Division Street
719753f-a.text:
Forsyth Street, east side, from Division Street to East Broadway.
Note the Second Ave. Elevated on Division Street.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
719753f-a.folder: Forsyth Street & Division Street, Manhattan, NY

719757f-a.title: Manhattan: Forsyth Street - Division Street
719757f-a.text:
Forsyth and Eldridge Streets, at their convergence at
Division Street. The latter thoroughfare is on the right and
is darkened by the ''El'' line thereupon. A gasoline station
appears at the apex formed. Forsyth Street is on the left
and Eldridge Street on the right. Overhead, though not shown
is the Manhattan Bridge (Canal Street).
April 6, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUTCTIONS

719310f-a.text:
(1)
8486 Division Street, north side, from Forsyth (left), to Eldridge
(right) Streets. Also shown is Eldridge Street, west side, north
from Division, to and including Canal Streets. The Elevated ou Di-
vision Street, is the Second Ave. Line.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
